(X', Y', Z', T') in extended ℙ³ representation (i.e., with X'/Z' = x, Y'/Z' = y and T' = X'Y'/Z')

natural language specs:

• The function always succeeds (no panic)
• Given an input completed point (X, Y, Z, T), the output EdwardsPoint (X', Y', Z', T')
satisfies:
- X' ≡ X·T (mod p)
- Y' ≡ Y·Z (mod p)
- Z' ≡ Z·T (mod p)
- T' ≡ X·Y (mod p)
where p = 2^255 - 19
